<p>(1) The net loss used in computing net loss per share has been increased by the accretion of the mandatorily redeemable convertible preferred stock to its redemption value in the fiscal year ended May 31, 1996 of $611.  </p>
<p>Note - During the fourth quarter, Verity completed two significant acquisitions which resulted in charges related to in-process research and development totaling $4.9 million, or $0.44 per share. Excluding these one-time charges, the net loss for the fourth quarter would have been $1.2 million, or $0.11 per share.</p>
<p>During the fiscal year, Verity completed three significant acquisitions which resulted in charges related to in-process research and development totaling $14.9 million, or $1.37 per share. Excluding these one-time charges, the net loss for the fiscal year would have been $3.0 million, or $0.28 per share.</p>
